<title>UK: Alliance/Leicester details share auction.</title>
<headline>Alliance/Leicester details share auction.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Alliance &amp; Leicester building society, in the process of converting to a bank with Plc status, said on Monday that it expected 27.5 percent of its issued share capital would be available to institutions under share auctions to start on April 18.</p>
<p>The society said the number of shares members had elected to sell (&quot;Sale Shares&quot;) was approximately 155 million, and was expected to total some 160 million shares, or 27.5 percent of the company's issued share capital.</p>
